    "title": "Two Sum",
    "description": "After the great meme reset of 2026, the number 67 became just an ordinary number with no significant meaning. It is not a funny number. It is not something to get all worked up over. End of story. \n\nRecently, there has been an epidemic in the usage of the number 67 at several high schools in a huge school district. Students have been claiming that 6 + 7 = 67 rather than the mathematically correct answer of 13. Each school has a different number of students affected by the epidemic. Fortunately, the school district was able to fund a single task force that can be deployed at a single school. Once deployed, it will be able to treat all students of that school and surrounding schools within a certain Manhattan distance (x distance + y distance). The high schools are arranged in a rectangular grid. \n\nYou are given N, the total number of high schools in the school district. You are given X, the number of rows in the rectangular grid. You are given Y, the number of columns in the rectangular grid. You are given X number of arrays, each containing Y number of elements. For each array, the ith element represents the number of students affected by the epidemic. You are given K, the Manhattan distance units that the task force can travel to treat surrounding schools. \n\nPlease help the school district locate the best school for the task force to treat the largest number of students.",
    "points": 100,
    "testCases": [
      { "input": "9 3 3 2\n5 7 12\n12 15 0\n1 4 20", "output": "2 2" },
